My hub picked up a 6 pack of this when we were in TN. Pours a warm golden color with a touch of haze. Ok aroma. A little orange-rind flavor, nice aftertaste. I like it!!

review_blob:
From the can, purchased from Craft and Draft in Columbia, SC. Pours golden, a touch hazy. Aroma is meh. Light bodied. Taste is a bit funky, not a fan of this flavor of hops--just a bit stinky. I can finish it but wouldn't buy again.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Light and tasty--perfect for summer! Purchased cans at Craft and Draft in Columbia, SC. Golden color, a tiny bit cloudy. Nice hoppy aroma. Light bodied. Slightly fruity. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

On draft at Krafty Draft in Lexington, SC. Smells yummy, lovely golden color. Light bodied. Unique hoppy flavor from the jade hops. Kinda lightly sweet, almost fruity.

On draft at Krafty Draft in Lexington, SC. Nice Amber color. light body, thin feel, average carbonation, bitter, I can drink it, but I wouldnt order another.
